================================================================================
WHAT IS DISTRIBUTED IN THIS REPOSITORY
================================================================================

This repository contains ONLY the orchestrator code, configuration files,
documentation and infrastructure of the pipeline:

    - scripts/        Python orchestrator and helper scripts
    - audit_lib/      Shared library used by the orchestrator
    - bin/            Bash entry points
    - wrappers/       Lightweight CLI adapters for tools whose own CLI is
                      missing or incompatible (small Python files, no model
                      weights)
    - config/         YAML configuration (pipeline_config.yaml,
                      pipeline_config_blocked.yaml, categories_config.yaml,
                      apex_strain_classification.yaml)
    - docs/           Project documentation
    - test_data/      Tiny FASTA samples for smoke testing

================================================================================
WHAT IS *NOT* DISTRIBUTED IN THIS REPOSITORY
================================================================================

The third-party prediction tools that the pipeline can orchestrate
(roughly two dozen evaluated; ten currently active — see
THIRD_PARTY_LICENSES.md and docs/pipeline_viability.md for the
authoritative inventory) are NOT included in this repository. Each
tool has its own license, its own repository, and its own model
weights. To run the full pipeline you must:

  1. Clone the upstream repositories yourself (URLs in
     docs/pipeline_viability.md and config/pipeline_config.yaml).
  2. Comply with each tool's license — see THIRD_PARTY_LICENSES.md.
  3. Place each tool under Dataset_Bioactividad/Tool_Repos/<tool_name>/.

Likewise, this repository does NOT redistribute:

  - Model weights or checkpoints (these belong to the original tool authors).
  - External peptide databases (DBAASP, APD3, ConoServer, ArachnoServer,
    Hemolytik, CancerPPD, CPPsite, BIOPEP, AVPdb). Download them yourself
    from the official sources and place them under DATABASES_FASTA/.

